In the 2016 Census, there were 6,923 people in Viewbank. Of these 49.6% were male and 50.4% were female. Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander people made up 0.5% of the population.

The most common ancestries in Viewbank were English 20.9%, Australian 20.3%, Italian 9.3%, Irish 8.2% and Chinese 7.9%.

Respondents had the option of reporting up to two ancestries on their Census form, and this is captured by the Ancestry Multi Response (ANCP) variable used in this table. Therefore, the total responses count will not equal the persons count for this area. Calculated percentages represent a proportion of all responses from people in Viewbank (including those who did not state an ancestry).
